The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 22 March is 251,015 (28,930.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 17 March, there were 9,920 new confirmed cases (1,143.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 10 March, there were 7,110 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 40% (2,810 extra cases).
